	<h4 class="process-title blue">Things to consider before writing a Thesis</h4>
	<p class="main-article">Thesis writing is an academic requirement. Institutions of higher education require students to write a thesis as it is one way of knowing the student’s learning level. While some students consider writing a thesis a boring task, writing a thesis is quite easy if one is aware of the necessary elements to consider before writing one. In the course of research, there are several articles, which enumerate the necessary things to consider in writing a thesis. The following are the key elements in preparing to write a thesis:</p>
	<h4 class="process-title">1. Be aware of your role as a researcher.</h4>
	<p class="main-article">As thesis writing requires objectivity and professionalism, be aware of the responsibilities and expectations as a researcher.</p>
	<h4 class="process-title">2. Be aware of your resources.</h4>
	<p class="main-article">Consider your technological resources including your knowledge in computer applications. Should your resources are not enough; do not hesitate to ask for help from your professors.</p>
	<h4 class="process-title">3. Choose a writing standard that you will follow.</h4>
	<p class="main-article">Clarify with your professor on what are the writing rules to follow. Be aware of the required writing standards such as citation rules and page set up.</p>
	<h4 class="process-title">4. Read other researches related to your topic.</h4>
	<p class="main-article">Be aware of the current development in your chosen field of study as you need to interact with those in the course of your research.</p>
	<h4 class="process-title">5. Think while writing. Do not just translate images into words.</h4>
